http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/3-booked-in-case-of-dowry-harassment/article13991983.ece

A Delhi court has upheld the framing of charges against the husband and parents-in-law of a woman for allegedly harassing, beating and criminally intimidating her for dowry in north-west Delhi’s Aya Nagar in 2009.According to the complaint lodged by the victim, her father-in-law demanded Rs. 5 lakh the day after she got married.After she returned form her father’s house, her mother-in-law complained that they had been given just one car and no cash.The woman alleged that she was abused and that her husband slapped her on the first night of the marriage.